article.headline: Saint Louis 77, Tennessee-Martin 53
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Dwayne Polk scored a career-high 17 points, and Saint Louis overcame an injury to its leading scorer in a 77-53 victory over Tennessee-Martin on Saturday night. Polk was one of four players in double figures for the Billikens (8-2). Luke Meyer scored 15 points, Tommie Liddell added 10 and Ian Vouyoukas had his fifth double-double of the season with 11 points and 10 rebounds. Saint Louis' victory came despite the absence of Kevin Lisch for most of the game. The left-handed guard, who averaged 15.9 points for entering Saturday's game, left with a laceration between the middle and ring fingers of his shooting hand. The injury required five stitches, and Lisch did not return after leaving with 7:29 left in the first half. He is expected back in time for the most important stretch of the Billikens' non-conference schedule. Saint Louis plays host to Missouri State on Monday, third-ranked North Carolina on Friday and Mississippi on Dec. 30. Saint Louis used strong runs at the start of both halves to pull away from Tennessee-Martin (3-8). The Billikens took an 11-0 lead to open the game and extended their 38-24 halftime lead with a 13-2 spurt over the first 4:21 following the break. Cleve Woodfork led the Skyhawks with 13 points.
